Weekly Exercise 2.

  1. The number of Airbnb units is so different in its observed auto correlation from the number of housing units likely from zoning regulation restricting where housing units can be used for AirBnb, human activity may also influence the results; AirBnbs will likely be situated close to and follow the clustered pattern of city centers and areas with high commercial/human activity.

  2. Morans I statistic for AirBnbs using a binary weights list is 0.66 with a significant p value. Morans I statistic for Housing units using a binary weights list is 0.53 with a significant p value. Both AirBnbs are highly clustered with AirBnBs having a slightly higher clustering. Similar results are found in the Geary calculation. Geary C statistic is 0.37 for Air BnB units and 0.47 for Housing units both values were statistically significant. Geary C numbers higher than 1 indicate negative spatial autocorrelation (dispersal) and numbers lower than one indicate positive spatial autocorrelation (clustering). The low numbers I calculated for AirBnb and Housing units indicate positive spatial autocorrelation. In addition, the p value is less than 0.05 so we must reject the null hypothesis.

  3. I calculated separate Morans I numbers for distances greater than half a mile and distances greater than one mile. The Morans I falls as the distance increases for two reasons.

  4. We observe an actual reduction in clustering and increase in dispersal of AirBnbs beyond the half a mile radius of city areas. 2.The above fact is exaggerated somewhat by creating an inverse distance matrix. If AirBnbs are actually clustered, the effect of clustering is decayed with distance in areas where we observe dispersal.

centroids <- st_centroid(hex_grid)
## Warning: st_centroid assumes attributes are constant over geometries
distances <- st_distance(centroids, centroids) %>%
set_units(NULL)
distances[distances > 2640] <- 0

miler <- st_distance(centroids, centroids) %>%
set_units(NULL)
miler[miler > 5280] <- 0
inverse_dist <- ifelse(distances!=0, 1/(distances^2),distances)
inverse_miler <- ifelse(miler!=0, 1/(miler^2),miler)
inverse_dist_listw <- mat2listw(inverse_dist, style="W")
inverse_miler_listw <- mat2listw(inverse_miler, style="W")

moran.test(x = hex_grid$abnb_count, listw = inverse_dist_listw)
